events.description: Drogo of Hauteville is elected as count of the Apulian Normans during the Norman conquest of Southern Italy.
events.html: • 1047 – Drogo of Hauteville is elected as count of the Apulian Normans during the Norman conquest of Southern Italy.[1]

events.description: Ramon Berenguer III, Count of Barcelona, and Douce I, Countess of Provence, marry, uniting the fortunes of those two states.
events.html: • 1112 – Ramon Berenguer III, Count of Barcelona, and Douce I, Countess of Provence, marry, uniting the fortunes of those two states.[2]

entities.name: Ramon Berenguer III, Count of Barcelona

events.description: Sultan Mehmed II inherits the throne of the Ottoman Empire.
events.html: • 1451 – Sultan Mehmed II inherits the throne of the Ottoman Empire.[3]

events.description: Bartolomeu Dias of Portugal lands in Mossel Bay after rounding the Cape of Good Hope, becoming the first known European to travel so far south.
events.html: • 1488 – Bartolomeu Dias of Portugal lands in Mossel Bay after rounding the Cape of Good Hope, becoming the first known European to travel so far south.[4]

events.description: The Portuguese navy defeats a joint fleet of the Ottoman Empire, the Republic of Venice, the Sultan of Gujarat, the Mamlûk Burji Sultanate of Egypt, the Zamorin of Calicut, and the Republic of Ragusa at the Battle of Diu in Diu, India.
events.html: • 1509 – The Portuguese navy defeats a joint fleet of the Ottoman Empire, the Republic of Venice, the Sultan of Gujarat, the Mamlûk Burji Sultanate of Egypt, the Zamorin of Calicut, and the Republic of Ragusa at the Battle of Diu in Diu, India.[5]

events.description: Battle of São Vicente takes place off Portuguese Brazil where three English warships led by navigator Edward Fenton fight off three Spanish galleons sinking one in the process.
events.html: • 1583 – Battle of São Vicente takes place off Portuguese Brazil where three English warships led by navigator Edward Fenton fight off three Spanish galleons sinking one in the process.[6]

events.description: Tulip Mania collapses within the Dutch Republic.
events.html: • 1637 – Tulip Mania collapses within the Dutch Republic.[7]

events.description: The House of Assembly of Barbados meets for the first time.
events.html: • 1639 – The House of Assembly of Barbados meets for the first time.[8]

events.description: The colony of Massachusetts issues the first paper money in the Americas.
events.html: • 1690 – The colony of Massachusetts issues the first paper money in the Americas.

events.description: During the Battle of Fraustadt Swedish forces defeat a superior Saxon-Polish-Russian force by deploying a double envelopment.
events.html: • 1706 – During the Battle of Fraustadt Swedish forces defeat a superior Saxon-Polish-Russian force by deploying a double envelopment.

events.description: The 1716 Algiers earthquake sequence began with an Mw  7.0 mainshock that caused severe damage and killed 20,000 in Algeria.
events.html: • 1716 – The 1716 Algiers earthquake sequence began with an Mw  7.0 mainshock that caused severe damage and killed 20,000 in Algeria.[9]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: British forces seize the Dutch-owned Caribbean island Sint Eustatius.
events.html: • 1781 – American Revolutionary War: British forces seize the Dutch-owned Caribbean island Sint Eustatius.

events.description: Spain–United States relations are first established.
events.html: • 1783 – Spain–United States relations are first established.

events.description: Militia led by General Benjamin Lincoln crush the remnants of Shays' Rebellion in Petersham, Massachusetts.
events.html: • 1787 – Militia led by General Benjamin Lincoln crush the remnants of Shays' Rebellion in Petersham, Massachusetts.

events.description: A British military force, under Brigadier-General Sir Samuel Auchmuty captures the Spanish Empire city of Montevideo, now the capital of Uruguay.
events.html: • 1807 – A British military force, under Brigadier-General Sir Samuel Auchmuty captures the Spanish Empire city of Montevideo, now the capital of Uruguay.

events.description: The Territory of Illinois is created by the 10th United States Congress.
events.html: • 1809 – The Territory of Illinois is created by the 10th United States Congress.

events.description: José de San Martín defeats a Spanish royalist army at the Battle of San Lorenzo, part of the Argentine War of Independence.
events.html: • 1813 – José de San Martín defeats a Spanish royalist army at the Battle of San Lorenzo, part of the Argentine War of Independence.[10]

events.description: The London Protocol of 1830 establishes the full independence and sovereignty of Greece from the Ottoman Empire as the final result of the Greek War of Independence.
events.html: • 1830 – The London Protocol of 1830 establishes the full independence and sovereignty of Greece from the Ottoman Empire as the final result of the Greek War of Independence.

events.description: Moldavia and Wallachia formally unite to create the Romanian United Principalities.
events.html: • 1862 – Moldavia and Wallachia formally unite to create the Romanian United Principalities.[11]

entities.name: United Principalities of Moldavia and Wallachia

events.description: The Fifteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, guaranteeing voting rights to male citizens regardless of race.
events.html: • 1870 – The Fifteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, guaranteeing voting rights to male citizens regardless of race.

entities.name: Fifteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution

events.description: The Sixteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, authorizing the Federal government to impose and collect an income tax.
events.html: • 1913 – The Sixteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, authorizing the Federal government to impose and collect an income tax.

entities.name: Sixteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution
Federal government of the United States

events.description: The Centre Block of the Parliament buildings in Ottawa, Ontario, Canada burns down with the loss of seven lives.
events.html: • 1916 – The Centre Block of the Parliament buildings in Ottawa, Ontario, Canada burns down with the loss of seven lives.

events.description: World War I: The American entry into World War I begins when diplomatic relations with Germany are severed due to its unrestricted submarine warfare.
events.html: • 1917 – World War I: The American entry into World War I begins when diplomatic relations with Germany are severed due to its unrestricted submarine warfare.

entities.name: American entry into World War I

events.description: The Twin Peaks Tunnel in San Francisco, California begins service as the longest streetcar tunnel in the world at 11,920 feet (3,630 meters) long.
events.html: • 1918 – The Twin Peaks Tunnel in San Francisco, California begins service as the longest streetcar tunnel in the world at 11,920 feet (3,630 meters) long.

events.description: A revolt against the military dictatorship of Portugal breaks out at Oporto.
events.html: • 1927 – A revolt against the military dictatorship of Portugal breaks out at Oporto.[12]

events.description: The Communist Party of Vietnam is founded at a "Unification Conference" held in Kowloon, British Hong Kong.
events.html: • 1930 – The Communist Party of Vietnam is founded at a "Unification Conference" held in Kowloon, British Hong Kong.

events.description: The Hawke's Bay earthquake, New Zealand's worst natural disaster, kills 258.
events.html: • 1931 – The Hawke's Bay earthquake, New Zealand's worst natural disaster, kills 258.

events.description: Adolf Hitler announces that the expansion of Lebensraum into Eastern Europe, and its ruthless Germanisation, are the ultimate geopolitical objectives of Nazi foreign policy.
events.html: • 1933 – Adolf Hitler announces that the expansion of Lebensraum into Eastern Europe, and its ruthless Germanisation, are the ultimate geopolitical objectives of Nazi foreign policy.

events.description: The SS Dorchester is sunk by a German U-boat. Only 230 of 902 men aboard survive.
events.html: • 1943 – The SS Dorchester is sunk by a German U-boat. Only 230 of 902 men aboard survive.

events.description: World War II: During the Gilbert and Marshall Islands campaign, U.S. Army and Marine forces seize Kwajalein Atoll from the defending Japanese garrison.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: During the Gilbert and Marshall Islands campaign, U.S. Army and Marine forces seize Kwajalein Atoll from the defending Japanese garrison.

events.description: World War II: As part of Operation Thunderclap, 1,000 B-17s of the Eighth Air Force bomb Berlin, a raid which kills between 2,500 and 3,000 and dehouses another 120,000.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: As part of Operation Thunderclap, 1,000 B-17s of the Eighth Air Force bomb Berlin, a raid which kills between 2,500 and 3,000 and dehouses another 120,000.

entities.name: Bombing of Berlin in World War II

events.description: World War II: The United States and the Philippine Commonwealth begin a month-long battle to retake Manila from Japan.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The United States and the Philippine Commonwealth begin a month-long battle to retake Manila from Japan.

events.description: The Batepá massacre occurred in São Tomé when the colonial administration and Portuguese landowners unleashed a wave of violence against the native creoles known as forros.
events.html: • 1953 – The Batepá massacre occurred in São Tomé when the colonial administration and Portuguese landowners unleashed a wave of violence against the native creoles known as forros.

events.description: Founding of the Benelux Economic Union, creating a testing ground for a later European Economic Community.
events.html: • 1958 – Founding of the Benelux Economic Union, creating a testing ground for a later European Economic Community.[13]

events.description: Rock and roll musicians Buddy Holly, Ritchie Valens, and J. P. "The Big Bopper" Richardson are killed in a plane crash along with the pilot near Clear Lake, Iowa, an event later known as The Day the Music Died.
events.html: • 1959 – Rock and roll musicians Buddy Holly, Ritchie Valens, and J. P. "The Big Bopper" Richardson are killed in a plane crash along with the pilot near Clear Lake, Iowa, an event later known as The Day the Music Died.

events.description: Sixty-five people are killed when American Airlines Flight 320 crashes into the East River on approach to LaGuardia Airport in New York City.
events.html: • 1959 – Sixty-five people are killed when American Airlines Flight 320 crashes into the East River on approach to LaGuardia Airport in New York City.[14]

events.description: British Prime Minister Harold Macmillan speaks of "a wind of change", signalling that his Government was likely to support decolonisation.
events.html: • 1960 – British Prime Minister Harold Macmillan speaks of "a wind of change", signalling that his Government was likely to support decolonisation.

entities.name: Prime Minister of the United Kingdom

events.description: The United States Air Force begins Operation Looking Glass, and over the next 30 years, a "Doomsday Plane" is always in the air, with the capability of taking direct control of the United States' bombers and missiles in the event of the destruction of the SAC's command post.
events.html: • 1961 – The United States Air Force begins Operation Looking Glass, and over the next 30 years, a "Doomsday Plane" is always in the air, with the capability of taking direct control of the United States' bombers and missiles in the event of the destruction of the SAC's command post.

events.description: The Soviet Union's Luna 9 becomes the first spacecraft to make a soft landing on the Moon, and the first spacecraft to take pictures from the surface of the Moon.
events.html: • 1966 – The Soviet Union's Luna 9 becomes the first spacecraft to make a soft landing on the Moon, and the first spacecraft to take pictures from the surface of the Moon.[15]

events.description: New York Police Officer Frank Serpico is shot during a drug bust in Brooklyn and survives to later testify against police corruption.
events.html: • 1971 – New York Police Officer Frank Serpico is shot during a drug bust in Brooklyn and survives to later testify against police corruption.[16]

events.description: The first day of the seven-day 1972 Iran blizzard, which would kill at least 4,000 people, making it the deadliest snowstorm in history.
events.html: • 1972 – The first day of the seven-day 1972 Iran blizzard, which would kill at least 4,000 people, making it the deadliest snowstorm in history.[17]

entities.name: List of natural disasters by death toll

events.description: Doctor John Buster and a research team at Harbor-UCLA Medical Center in the United States announce history's first embryo transfer, from one woman to another resulting in a live birth.
events.html: • 1984 – Doctor John Buster and a research team at Harbor-UCLA Medical Center in the United States announce history's first embryo transfer, from one woman to another resulting in a live birth.[18]

events.description: Space Shuttle program: STS-41-B is launched using Space Shuttle Challenger.
events.html: • 1984 – Space Shuttle program: STS-41-B is launched using Space Shuttle Challenger.

events.description: After a stroke two weeks previously, South African President P. W. Botha resigns as leader of the National Party, but stays on as president for six more months.
events.html: • 1989 – After a stroke two weeks previously, South African President P. W. Botha resigns as leader of the National Party, but stays on as president for six more months.

events.description: A military coup overthrows Alfredo Stroessner, dictator of Paraguay since 1954.
events.html: • 1989 – A military coup overthrows Alfredo Stroessner, dictator of Paraguay since 1954.

events.description: Space Shuttle program: STS-60 is launched, carrying Sergei Krikalev, the first Russian cosmonaut to fly aboard the Shuttle.
events.html: • 1994 – Space Shuttle program: STS-60 is launched, carrying Sergei Krikalev, the first Russian cosmonaut to fly aboard the Shuttle.[19]

events.description: Astronaut Eileen Collins becomes the first woman to pilot the Space Shuttle as mission STS-63 gets underway from Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
events.html: • 1995 – Astronaut Eileen Collins becomes the first woman to pilot the Space Shuttle as mission STS-63 gets underway from Kennedy Space Center in Florida.

events.description: Cavalese cable car disaster: A United States military pilot causes the death of 20 people when his low-flying plane cuts the cable of a cable-car near Trento, Italy.
events.html: • 1998 – Cavalese cable car disaster: A United States military pilot causes the death of 20 people when his low-flying plane cuts the cable of a cable-car near Trento, Italy.[20]

events.description: One hundred five people are killed when Kam Air Flight 904 crashes in the Pamir Mountains in Afghanistan.
events.html: • 2005 – One hundred five people are killed when Kam Air Flight 904 crashes in the Pamir Mountains in Afghanistan.[21]

events.description: A Baghdad market bombing kills at least 135 people and injures a further 339.
events.html: • 2007 – A Baghdad market bombing kills at least 135 people and injures a further 339.

events.description: Two people are shot and killed and 29 students are taken hostage at a high school in Moscow, Russia.
events.html: • 2014 – Two people are shot and killed and 29 students are taken hostage at a high school in Moscow, Russia.

events.description: 2023 Ohio train derailment: A freight train containing vinyl chloride and other hazardous materials derails and burns in East Palestine, Ohio, United States, releasing hydrogen chloride and phosgene into the air and contaminating the Ohio River.
events.html: • 2023 – 2023 Ohio train derailment: A freight train containing vinyl chloride and other hazardous materials derails and burns in East Palestine, Ohio, United States, releasing hydrogen chloride and phosgene into the air and contaminating the Ohio River.[22]
